      <intermediateExchange id="d3850976-75ad-50be-96a1-89d885506e4d" unitId="77ae64fa-7e74-4252-9c3b-889c1cd20bfc" amount="0.4527514571250665" intermediateExchangeId="759b89bd-3aa6-42ad-b767-5bb9ef5d331d" activityLinkId="7a4d8ad6-3116-52f6-a46f-6b21b52d4df3">
        <name xml:lang="en">electricity, medium voltage</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kWh</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">According to personal communications with Lonza (in 2003), the catalytic oxidation of benzene to maleic anhydride requires 0.6 kWh of electricity per kg of maleic anhydride (Althaus, 2007). At the same time, Chauvel and Lefebvre (1989) reported a value of 1.5 kWh of electricity per kg of maleic anhydride. We, here, use the most up-to-date value, i.e., the personal communications with Lonza, in alignment with the heat output source.

References:
Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.
Personal communication, Giovanni.Montiglio, Lonza, May 2003
Chauvel, Alain, Gilles Lefebvre, and L. Castex in "Petrochemical processes. Technical and economical characteristics Vol. 2." (1989).</comment>
        <uncertainty>
